choices.text:
a taboo subject. This suggests that as long as talking about it remains disproportionately difficult because of social pressures, teens will continue to direct their feelings of guilt and confusion towards themselves - which is the last thing they need.

They need to know that it is all ok; that being sad is of course totally normal and they don't need to hide away in shame and remorse.

That’s why I think NRS is so important - it turns the conversation around for teens, and takes away the taboo from such painful topics as abortion, miscarriage, mental health, long-term contraception and abortion.

While I know it is chock-full of medical information, I would urge you to really listen to their podcasts as well, because that’s when the real messages come across.

Information on abortion itself can be easy to find, but proper, accurate, balanced and tailored information for teens is a real rarity. NRS’s aim is to change this, and I’m as passionate about this as it gets.
